DIV1.P: An Extraordinary COLLECTION Of ORIGINAL PICTURES Will be SOLD by AUCTION,
At the Three-Tun Tavern in Witch-street, be∣hind St. Clement's Church; on Monday, the Ninth of this instant November, 1691. and the Two following Days.
The SALE will begin at Three each After∣noon.
The PICTURES are ready to be View'd, and CATALOGUES to be Delivered to all Gentlemen, &c. please to repair to the Place of SALE.

DIV1.HEAD: The CONDITIONS of Sale.
DIV1.P: THE highest Bidder is to be deemed the Buyer.
The Buyers are to give in their Names and Place of Abode, and to pay a Third part of the Value, if desired, or to be put up again.
But if any two or more shall claim any Lott, then the Said Lott to be Exposed to Sale again.
The Buyer is to pay for and take away what Pictures, &c. shall be bought, within Three Days after the Sale.
No Person to bid less than Six Pence at a Time.
And for the satisfaction of the Company pre∣sent, it is engaged, That no Proprietors of any Paintings, &c. shall bid for their own Goods.
